node.text:
Having lunch break from my online lesson. Having #hbl myself, I can see both the good and bad about this. All I can say is that, I prefer to go back to school for classroom learning. Nothing beats having the face to face interactions and support from teacher and fellow mates!

Alright now back to enjoying my cod fillets from @mr.fishmongersg using recipe from @themeatmensg of course. The cod is super fresh and sweet!! Link: https://youtu.be/Mfxl5SClMr4
@danceyedna yeah better than nothing. Though I can’t wait to go back to school! 😂  Thank you, hun!
I too agree that online learning is not the best way... however for short term.. it’s better then nothing.  Yum.  The cod fillets looks absolutely yummy!😂
😋😋 you made the cod fish look so tasty!
@fj.mama didn’t use shallots for this. Ingredients used are spring onions, gingers, garlics, soy sauce, sugar, hua tiao wine and sesame oil! 😊
@happyzboys aww!!! The fried garlic looks like shallots!!!
@fj.mama lol cos I chose the fat and big ones! 😊 I love garlics!!
@coffeecake888 I have lotsa help! 😊😊 Mainly the 👍🏻 recipe from @themeatmensg
You are such a good cook!👩‍🍳 👍🏻 😋
@happy_lady27 awesome!! You will like @mr.fishmongersg seafood like I do! 👍🏻
Thanks for sharing ya dear I already followed you to make order 😋😇
